Q1.What is the total number of Reported Deliveries in Karnataka over 3 years?¶

In [12]:
#Total Number of reporated delivaries
sums = names.groupby('Year')['Total reported deliveries'].sum()
years = list(sums.keys())
# Plotting the bar graph
bars = plt.bar(years, sums,color='y')

# Adding labels and title
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Deliveries')
plt.title('Total Number of Deliveries by Year')

# Set the y-axis limits
plt.ylim([870000, 930000])

# Display the values on top of each bar
for bar in bars:
    height = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, height, str(height),
             ha='center', va='bottom')

# Display the graph
plt.show()

Inference:¶

This graph shows the total number of Reported deliveries year by year.¶

-In 2017-18 , highest reported Deliveries are there as compared to 2018-19 and 2019-20.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

labels = ["Bangalore Division", "Belagum Division", "Kalburgi Division", "Mysore Division"]
year_1 = [268860,258560,230505,157319]
year_2 = [272292,249977,219127,158114]  # Replace these values with data for the second year
year_3 = [288415,238663,219585,151796]  # Replace these values with data for the third year

bar_width = 0.25  # Width of each bar
bar_positions_1 = list(range(len(labels)))
bar_positions_2 = [pos + bar_width for pos in bar_positions_1]
bar_positions_3 = [pos + bar_width * 2 for pos in bar_positions_1]

# Horizontal bar chart with custom colors
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))
bars1 = plt.bar(bar_positions_1, year_1, width=bar_width, color="chocolate", label='Year 1')
bars2 = plt.bar(bar_positions_2, year_2, width=bar_width, color="orange", label='Year 2')
bars3 = plt.bar(bar_positions_3, year_3, width=bar_width, color="crimson", label='Year 3')

# Title and labels
plt.title('Total Number of Live Births Division wise')
plt.xlabel('Administration divisions')
plt.ylabel('Death')

# Display the values on top of each bar for year 1
for i, bar in enumerate(bars1):
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, bar.get_height(),
             year_1[i], ha='center', va='bottom')

# Display the values on top of each bar for year 2
for i, bar in enumerate(bars2):
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, bar.get_height(),
             year_2[i], ha='center', va='bottom')

# Display the values on top of each bar for year 3
for i, bar in enumerate(bars3):
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, bar.get_height(),
             year_3[i], ha='center', va='bottom')

# Set the x-axis ticks and labels
plt.xticks([pos + bar_width for pos in bar_positions_1], labels)

# Add a legend
plt.legend()

# Display the chart
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Q3.What is the total number of live births district-wise?¶

In [11]:
fig, ax=plt.subplots(figsize=(16,8))
sns.barplot(data=names, x="District", y="Total Number of reported live births", hue = 'Year',ax=ax)
ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(),rotation=50,horizontalalignment='right')
plt.title("Number of Live Births District wise")
plt.show()

Inference:¶

-In 2017-18, Bangalore Urban has recorded highest number of live births and Kodagu the least.

-In 2018-19, Bangalore Urban has recorded highest number of live births and Kodagu the least.

-In 2019-20, Bangalore Urban has recorded highest number of live births and Kodagu the least.

-Overall population of the Bangalore Urban is more as compared to other district so it will be the one reason for increasing the number of live births in Bangalore Urban year to year.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

labels = ["% Deaths due to Sepsis", "% Deaths due to Asphyxia", "% Deaths due to Pneumonia",
          "% Deaths due to Diarrhoea", "% Deaths due to Fever", "% Deaths due to Measles"]
sizes = [8.25, 12.29, 5.09, 0.567, 1.172, 0.17]

plt.axis("equal")
plt.show()

Inference:¶

-This graph depicts the causes of infant death in Karnataka.

-The %death is highest due to Asphyxia and the least is due to Measles.

plt.ylabel('count')
plt.title('Number of infants received Rotavirus Vaccine 1st dose')

# Set the y-axis limits
plt.ylim([0, 1000000])

# Display the values on top of each bar

    height = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, height, str(height),
             ha='center', va='bottom')

# Display the graph
plt.show()

Inference:¶

-Number of infants that have received Rotavirus Vaccination has increased from year to year.

-But substantially the intake of 2nd & 3rd dose has been decreased compared to 1st dose.

-Rotavirus vaccination is given to the infant to prevent them from getting infected with Diarrhoea (caused by rotavirus).

BCG Vaccine¶

BCG, or Bacille Calmette-Guerin, is a vaccine for tuberculosis (TB) disease to prevent childhood tuberculous meningitis(Brain Fever) and miliary disease(tubercle bacilli to the lungs).¶
